ew analyses of such classic films as Bringing Up Baby, The Thin Man, Twentieth Century, Laura, To Have and Have Not, Tea and Sympathy, Written on the Wind, and more.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aLove in motion pictures. 0aMotion picture actingxCaliforniaxLos AngelesxUnited StatesxHistory. 0aMotion picturesxHistoryx20th centuryxCaliforniaxLos Angeles. 0aMotion picturesxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aMotion picturesxProduction and directionxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 4aAmerican Studies : American Culture. 4aCultural Studies : Popular Culture. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Mass Media. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2017z978311149102840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438465531423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438465531/original  a978-3-11-149102-8  SUNY Press eBook Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles